<h1>Task Description <small>What is this task all about?</small></h1>
</div>
<p>
	In this task, you will be annotating scientific papers with details about the <b>type</b> of citations. When you annotate for the scientific papers, you will need to read through a set of <b>citing papers</b> to look for <b>citing sentences</b> and a set of <b>cited papers</b> to look for the <b>cited information</b>. Finally for each citation, you will annotate by selecting the lines in the cited paper which you think is where the cited information.
</p>
<h2>Task Objective</h2>
<p>
The objective of this task is to gather manual annotations for our research. We wish to determine the type of the citation. There is a total of <b>3 types</b> of citation. Find out more <%= link_to "here", citation_path %>.
</p>
